        Over the past 20 years, the Institute has [published influential research](https://www.lowyinstitute.org/publications) with an eye to the topics that matter to Australia. The Institute’s interests are as broad as Australia’s interests. Institute scholars have examined Australia’s place in the world. They have explored the global role of the United States, highlighted the emergence of India and analysed the rising power of China. They have re-thought Australian policy in the Pacific and mapped global aid flows in the region. Researchers have published cutting-edge research on climate change, global diasporas and Asia’s changing power dynamics.

